# Premium Intelligence Web OS (Cursor)

When building any web UI/visual in this repo, follow the Premium Intelligence Web OS.

Read first: `premium-web-os/_intelligence/operating-system.md`, `taste.md`, `brand-worlds.md`.

Build sequence (non-negotiable):
read docs → page spec → scene brief → static composition → motion → 3D → polish → QA → decision log.

Hard rules:
- Don't build from a vague adjective — write a scene brief first (`_intelligence/templates/scene-brief.template.md`).
- Don't animate everything — one cinematic moment per page; motion serves hierarchy (`_intelligence/motion.md`).
- No raw hex in app code — bind to the brand token source (`_intelligence/brand-worlds.md`).
- No dep that isn't in package.json without a logged justification; verify APIs from source.
- No 3D without static poster fallback + mobile simplification + reduced-motion (`_intelligence/three-webgl.md`).
- No stock SaaS layouts, random gradients, emoji/glyph icons, equal-card grids.
- Everything responsive; mobile (375px) first-class. Ship only after the release checklist passes.

Full system: `premium-web-os/_intelligence/`.
